===Etymology===
Perhaps {{der|zh|sit}}. Compare {{cog|cdm|tr=maiʔ|t=meat}}, {{cog|brx|tr=bʏiʔ|t=deer}}, {{cog|njn|tr=ka-'''mî'''|t=meat}}, Northern Naga *''me:y'' "meat, flesh"; a single etymon for "meat" and "deer" is also found in {{cog|bo|ཤ|t=meat}} and {{m|bo|ཤྭ|t=deer}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). If so, another semantic parallel is {{cog|sit-pro|*tə-la||flesh, meat, deer}}, whence {{cog|bo|གླ||musk deer}} but {{cog|new|tr=la|t=meat, animal}} and {{m|new|tr=lā|t=flesh, meat}}.

